<section xml:id="reusing-classes_vocabulary" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<title>Vocabulary</title>
<p><dl>
<li>
<title>refactor:</title>
<p>
    <idx><h>refactor</h></idx>
To restructure or reorganize existing source code without changing its behavior.</p></li>
<li>
<title>abstract class:</title>
<p>
    <idx><h>abstract class</h></idx>
A class that is declared as <pf>abstract</pf>; it cannot be instantiated, and it may (or may not) include abstract functions.</p></li>
<li>
<title>concrete class:</title>
<p>
    <idx><h>concrete class</h></idx>
A class that is <term>not</term> declared as <pf>abstract</pf>; each of its functions must have an implementation.</p></li>
</dl></p>
</section>
